{[#] Black intends to play Qc7 in order to continue his development, with Rc8
and a possible initiative in queenside. Having this in mind White played
White's queen disturbs the coordination of Black's forces. How should Black
solve this problem?} 16... Re8 $1 {[%csl Rb7][%cal Ge7f8,Ge8e7] Suddenly the
queen is in trouble.} 17. c4 $2 {Overlooking the idea.} (17. a3 Bf8 18. Qc6 (
18. Rd2 Re6 $1 {[%cal Gd6d5,Ge6b6] very subtle and yet a strong move}) 18...
Qb8 19. Qc3 Rd8 $13 {[%cal Gd6d5]}) (17. Qc6 $142 Qb8 18. Qc3 Rc8 19. Qd3 Rd8
$13 {[%cal Yd6d5]}) 17... Bf8 $1 18. Qc6 $2 (18. cxb5 Re7 19. Qc6 Rc7 20. Qb6
Rc1+ $1 $19) (18. c5 Re7 19. Qc6 (19. Qb6 Qxb6 20. cxb6 Rb7 $17) 19... Rc7 20.
Qb6 Nd7 $17 {[%csl Yb6,Yc5]}) 18... Qb8 $1 {[%cal Ge8c8]} 19. Na5 Qa7 $1 {
The weak dark squares in White's camp start telling.} 20. c5 (20. cxb5 axb5 21.
b4 d5 $19) (20. Qb7 Qf2 21. Rd2 Rab8 22. Qxa6 Ra8 23. Qxb5 Reb8 24. Qa4 Qc5 $19
) 20... dxc5 $17 {Duda,J (2579)-Yu,Y (2668) Tromsoe ol (Men) 41st 2014 (11.3)
0-1} *

