compared with Black's structure which is totally homogeneous.} 24. c3 Nc7 25.
Rb6 d5 26. Rb7 e6 $11 {Black displayed great precision and tactical skills to
prove that the queenside pawns are not advancing so easily even when White is
a great positional player and a master of technique. Black even managed to
win in Adams, M (2715)-Nepomniachtchi, I (2729) 9th London Classic 2017 2017 (6.
4) 0-1} *

