bit unpleasant for Black in practice}) 13. O-O (13. g5 $6 Ne8 14. h4 {I think
such ideas are too optimistic, as White over-extends his structure on the
kingside with no real attacking chances, because Black is very solid.} g6 15.
Nd5 Bxd5 16. exd5 {Starostits,I (2330)-Solodovnichenko,Y (2415) Ceske
