$3 22. gxh7+ Kh8 $13 {White is 3 (!) pawns up but his position seems a bit
risky now.} 23. O-O Nxe3 24. Qxe3 Rc7 $44 {[%cal Yc7h7,Yh7h1]}) 13... g6 $1 {
preventing Nf5 is always a good idea after 0-0} 14. f4 $5 {White should open
the kingside, otherwise he could face some problems on the weakened
