15... dxe5 {and Black is ok if White plays the greedy} 16. axb5 axb5 17. Qxd8
Rfxd8 18. Rxa8 Rxa8 19. g5 Ne8 20. Nxb5 $2 {he will be in trouble after} Ba6
21. c4 Nd3 $1 {[%csl Gb2,Gg5][%cal Yd3c1]} 22. h4 Rc8 $17) 8... b5 {Black has
many options but again I like this move which strives for a quick development
on the queenside. In recent games, White has preferred} 9. Nd5 {[%cal Ge2c3]
with the idea to improve the Ne2 as soon as possible. This move has gained
popularity in the last few years and can be considered the main move at the
high level.} (9. a4 {is harmless now} b4 10. Nd5 Nxd5 11. Qxd5 Ra7 12. Be3 Be6
$1 {[%csl Ge2] because the knight has a poor position compared to the 7.Nb3
