Rfc8 $1 {and Black's counterplay seems enough to keep the position equal} 16.
Nd1 a5 $1 17. Ne3 (17. Bxd6 Qd7 {[%csl Yd6][%cal Yd7d2]} 18. Qd3 Nc4 $1 $17)
17... b4 18. Bb2 Nd7 $11 19. Rfd1 (19. Rad1 Ra6) 19... Bg5 $1) 11... Qxe7 12.
Bg5 (12. a4 {was played by Anand in a rapid game} b4 13. a5 $6 (13. Na2 $142 a5
14. c3 bxc3 15. Nxc3 O-O 16. O-O $11) 13... bxc3 14. axb6 cxb2 15. Bxb2 Rb8 $15
{[%csl Gb6] and Black simply won a pawn - Anand, V (2759) -Grischuk, A (2766)
