-Asis Gargatagli, H (2487) ESP-ch 80th Linares 2015 (6) 1/2-1/2 was also
harmless for Black} Qc7 $1 {[%cal Gb6c4] preparing Nc4 without fearing Bg5.} (
12... Nc4 13. Bg5 $1) 13. a4 b4 14. Bxb6 Qxb6 15. Nd5 Nxd5 16. Qxd5 Rb8 17. O-O
Be6 18. Qd2 O-O $11 {and Black is totally fine}) 12... O-O {It is important to complete the development first.} (12... h6 {gave White a tiny advantage after}
13. Bxf6 Qxf6 14. a4 bxa4 (14... b4 $2 15. Nd5 Nxd5 16. Qxd5 Ra7 17. Qc6+ Bd7
18. Qb6 $16 {[%csl Ra7,Rb4]}) 15. Nxa4 Nxa4 16. Rxa4 {[%csl Ga6,Gd6] White had
a small but long-lasting advantage due to his better pawn structure - Giri, A 
