b5 $1 $132) 11... Bxd5 12. exd5 a5 $5 {Nepo's attempt} (12... Nc5 {was played
by some strong players, but after} 13. Nxc5 dxc5 14. c4 {[%csl Gd5] we can see
the advantages of Bd2} Qc7 15. Rae1 Bd6 16. Qh3 $1 {first: the queen has the
third rank available to maneuver to the kingside} Rfe8 17. Bc3 $1 {[%csl Yc3]
[%cal Yd2c3] second: White can improve the bishop via c3} g6 18. Bd3 {[%csl
Gc3,Gd3,Yh3][%cal Gc3h8,Gd3h7] White is well developed and his bishops exert
