f5 22. f3 $16 {[%cal Gg3g4] White's assets are the passed pawn on d5, a well-developed position and Black's center and kingside remain under strong
pressure. White should slowly improve his position and wait for the right
moment to break into Black's camp. He eventually managed to do it by means of
g3-g4 in Nepomniachtchi, I (2751)-Gelfand, B (2724) Zuerich Chess Challenge 6th
2017 (4) 1-0}) 13. a4 {maybe a disadvantage of Bd2 is that White should commit
the queenside to avoid a4} (13. Qb5 {Black embarked now in some complications
with} a4 $1 14. Na5 Nc5 15. b4 axb3 16. axb3 Qc7 17. f3 e4 $1 18. b4 exf3 19.
gxf3 Ncd7 {[%csl Yc2]} 20. c4 Rfb8 21. Be3 Bf8 {and the position remained
tense, but White had problems with the misplaced queen on b5 - Rigo, Z (2391)
