{[%evp 0,11,-7,-14,-16,-16,-35,-16,-18,-17,-20,-6,-6,1]} {What's the easiest
path to solve Black's opening problems and reach equality?} 13... Nb6 $1 {
[%csl Yc4,Yd5] First Black must prevent White from establishing a firm control
over d5 which would have been possible after Rfd1 on the next move.} 14. Nxb6 (
14. Nxf6+ Qxf6 15. Bxe6 Qxe6 {[%csl Gb6] is an improvement for Black, as the
knight is usually more useful than the bishop in this position}) 14... Qxb6 15.
Bb3 (15. Bxe6 fxe6 16. c3 d5 $5 {[%cal Yc8c4]}) 15... Qc6 $1 {[%csl Gd5][%cal
Yc6c2] The next step is to attack c2 whist keeping an eye on d5.} 16. c3 Rfd8
17. Rfd1 Bxb3 18. axb3 d5 $1 $11 {and Black equalizes.} *

