{[%evp 0,11,-38,-43,-45,-35,-42,-57,-43,-39,-40,-37,-57,-38]} 14... a5 $1 {
Black secures the queenside pawns and improves the light-squared bishop.} 15.
g4 Ba6 16. Re1 {[%cal Ge2g3,Gg3f5] Black missed a nice positional idea here.
Find it.} Rc8 (16... Bxe2 $1 17. Qxe2 Bg5 $1 {[%csl Gd7,Yg2] would be very
good as Black achieves the best endgame possible, Knight vs Bishop, since the
light-squared bishop is the White's bad one, and the knight has many strong
posts at its disposal, like b6, c5, f6 or f4. Black would definitely have
better chances in the ensuing endgames.}) 17. Ng3 $1 {Now the chance it is
gone.} g6 (17... Bg5 $1 {would be still good}) 18. Bh6 Re8 19. Qd2 Nc5 $11 {
Assumpcao, R (2177)-Quintiliano Pinto, R (2487) Goiania STD-ch sf 2016 (6) 0-1
Black still had an easier game} *

