{[%evp 0,8,-15,-25,-14,32,6,28,9,62,24]} {An important thing in such positions
is an accurate feeling of the subtle strategic dangers contained in some
positions. It means that we should be aware of the opponent's plans to not end
up in an unpleasant position. The following example is instructive in this
regard. How would you play as Black?} 13... Nc5 $1 (13... O-O $2 {Natural, but
soon Black was going to regret his careless play.} 14. Nf1 $1 {Now, White
achieves a pleasant and stable advantage.} Rfe8 (14... Nc5 15. Bg5 $1 Ne6 16.
Bxf6 Bxf6 17. Ne3 Nd4 18. Qd3 $14 {[%csl Yd5]}) 15. Ne3 g6 16. Bd2 Qb8 17. Be1
$14 {[%cal Yc3d5] ;Valerga,D (2451)-Quintiliano Pinto,R (2469) Mercosur Cup
21st 2017 (3) 1-0 Black's position is very unpleasant as there is no clear
plan to contest White advantage, and White won in.}) 14. Nf1 Ne6 $1 15. Ne3 Nd4
16. Qd3 O-O 17. Bd2 {Felgaer,R (2574)-Fusco, L (2365) ARG-ch sf 82nd 2008 (4)
1-0} g6 {and the chances are even} *

