{[%evp 0,12,43,-21,-1,-12,28,-14,27,-17,31,27,46,51,45]} {What is the best
continuation for Black?} 14... Nxd5 $1 {Usually Black should keep the knights
in this structure, but in this case he can accelerate the advance of the
f-pawn by removing the knight from f6.} 15. exd5 Bg5 $1 {Another point is that
now he can exchange the bad bishop.} (15... f5 $6 16. Rab1 $1 {was also
interesting}) 16. c4 Bxe3 17. fxe3 $1 {White plays in order to make the
kingside initiative less dangerous.} a5 $1 {[%cal Gb7a6] Black continues
improving his pieces in a very instructive way.} 18. Rab1 Ba6 19. Qd2 Nb6 $132
{Sosa,T (2390)-Mareco,S (2599) ARG-ch 90th Buenos Aires 2015 (8) 0-1} *

