{[%evp 0,20,14,7,21,2,38,28,31,-26,10,-18,-19,-25,-25,-14,-27,-25,-25,-27,-24,
-29,-53] [#]} {Find the best way to face White standard plan Nb4-d5.} 15... b6
$1 {Accurate.} (15... b5 $2 {is inferior because White is not obligated to
capture the pawn. Instead he can continue with} 16. Nb4 $1 {establishing an
annoying grip on the queenside, for example} Qc5 17. Ncd5 $1 Bxd5 18. exd5 $14
{[%csl Gc6][%cal Yb4c6]}) 16. axb6 Nxb6 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Yb6c4] Threatening
Nc4 and at the same time improving the control over d5.} 17. Nb4 a5 {This
forces many exchanges that solve Black's position.} 18. Nbd5 Nfxd5 19. Nxd5
Nxd5 20. exd5 Bd7 {Black has solved the problem of the d5 square
satisfactorily and still keeps pressure on the queenside.} 21. Bc3 a4 $1 22.
Ra3 Qc5 23. g3 Bd8 $1 $15 {[%cal Yd8b6,Yd8a5] ;Valerga,D (2452)-Mareco,S (2648)
Villa Martelli zt 2.5 2017 (8) 0-1 And Black's position seems already easier
to play -} *

