{Find Black's best idea in this position.} 25... b4 $1 {White's king's
position is slowly but surely getting ripped open whereas White has not yet
started his play on the kingside.} 26. cxb4 Qb6 $1 27. Bxc4 Rxc4 28. Nc2 Rfc8
$1 {The f7 pawn is not really so important as the king can safely hide on f7.
Yet it made sense to take the pawn and then play Rd2.} 29. Rd2 (29. Qxf7+ Kh8
30. Rd2 Qc6 31. Qf2 Qxe4 (31... a5 {was played by Magnus in the game.}) 32. Re2
$13 {and White has chances to defend although the position remains complex.})
29... Qc6 (29... Qc7 $1 {would be better, protecting f7}) 30. Qxf7+ Kh8 31. Qf2
a5 32. a3 $2 (32. bxa5 $142 Rb8 33. b3 Rc3 $40) 32... axb4 33. Nxb4 Qxe4+ 34.
Ka2 Rxb4 $1 35. axb4 Ra8+ 36. Kb3 Rb8 $40 {Duda,J (2663)-Carlsen,M (2834)
Qatar Masters op 2015 (4) 0-1 And White got a strong attack in} *

