{[%evp 0,14,-26,-32,-31,-42,-33,-25,-46,-65,-33,-33,-38,-55,-78,-89,-83] [#]} {
White gave priority to the plan of establishing maximum control over d5 in the
first moves, but Black has a nice way to contest his plan. Find the idea!} 
17... b5 $1 {Of course, in order to achieve his goal White has delayed his
development, so Black can take advantage of it and play actively as the White
king in the center provides enough tactical resources.} 18. O-O (18. axb5 axb5
19. Rxa8 Qxa8 {[%csl Ye4] and Black is fine, for example} 20. Ncd5 (20. O-O
Ncxe4 21. Nxe4 Nxe4 22. Qd3 f5 23. Qxb5 d5 $15) 20... Nxd5 21. Nxd5 Bxd5 22.
exd5 Bg5 $1 $15) 18... bxa4 $5 19. Ned5 (19. Nxa4 Ncxe4) 19... Nxd5 20. Nxd5
Bg5 $1 21. Bxg5 hxg5 22. Nc3 Qd7 $1 {[%csl Ga4][%cal Yg5g4]} 23. h3 Rab8 $17 {
Kanmazalp, O (2473)-Ivanchuk, V (2713) 19th ch-EUR Indiv 2018 (1.5) 0-1 Black is
a pawn up and much better -} *

